-- More Russian Regions Said in Drought Emergencies by Interfax
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2012-07-25T09:57:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-25/more-russian-regions-said-in-drought-emergencies-by-interfax.html
More agricultural regions in Russia
declared emergencies because of a drought, Interfax reported.  The Orenburg region near the  Ural Mountains  declared an
emergency today, the  news agency  said. The Kurgan region and the
Republic of Bashkortostan also were affected, Interfax said,
citing regional data.  A further 20 regions are suffering from drought and extreme
heat, according to Ministry of Agriculture data. Crops were lost
on 1.5 million hectares (3.7 million acres), Interfax said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
